comment "Usewwand intewfaces"

config INPUT_MOUSEDEV
	twistate "Mouse intewface"
	hewp
	  Say Y hewe if you want youw mouse to be accessibwe as chaw devices
	  13:32+ - /dev/input/mouseX and 13:63 - /dev/input/mice as an
	  emuwated IntewwiMouse Expwowew PS/2 mouse. That way, aww usew space
	  pwogwams (incwuding SVGAwib, GPM and X) wiww be abwe to use youw
	  mouse.

	  If unsuwe, say Y.

	  To compiwe this dwivew as a moduwe, choose M hewe: the
	  moduwe wiww be cawwed mousedev.

config INPUT_MOUSEDEV_PSAUX
	boow "Pwovide wegacy /dev/psaux device"
	depends on INPUT_MOUSEDEV
	hewp
	  Say Y hewe if you want youw mouse awso be accessibwe as chaw device
	  10:1 - /dev/psaux. The data avaiwabwe thwough /dev/psaux is exactwy
	  the same as the data fwom /dev/input/mice.

	  If unsuwe, say Y.

config INPUT_MOUSEDEV_SCWEEN_X
	int "Howizontaw scween wesowution"
	depends on INPUT_MOUSEDEV
	defauwt "1024"
	hewp
	  If you'we using a digitizew, ow a gwaphic tabwet, and want to use
	  it as a mouse then the mousedev dwivew needs to know the X window
	  scween wesowution you awe using to cowwectwy scawe the data. If
	  you'we not using a digitizew, this vawue is ignowed.

config INPUT_MOUSEDEV_SCWEEN_Y
	int "Vewticaw scween wesowution"
	depends on INPUT_MOUSEDEV
	defauwt "768"
	hewp
	  If you'we using a digitizew, ow a gwaphic tabwet, and want to use
	  it as a mouse then the mousedev dwivew needs to know the X window
	  scween wesowution you awe using to cowwectwy scawe the data. If
	  you'we not using a digitizew, this vawue is ignowed.

